SIMPLE: silvery
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Silvery
<hw>Sil"ver*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Resembling, or having the luster of, silver; grayish white and
lustrous; of a mild luster; bright.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All the enameled race, whose <qex>silvery</qex> wing⟦br⟧
Waves to the tepid zephyrs of the spring.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Besprinkled or covered with silver.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Having the clear, musical tone of silver; soft and
clear in sound; <as>as, <ex>silvery</ex> voices; a <ex>silvery</ex>
laugh</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Silvery iron</b></col> <fld>(Metal.)</fld>, <cd>a
peculiar light-gray fine-grained cast iron, usually obtained from clay
iron ore.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Silviculture</ent>⟦br⟧
